Tutor: Peggy Fisher.

- July, 2014, IEEE, the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers, published a list of the top 10 programming languages.
- And the no 1 is Java
- During this course we will:
  - Take a quick tour of a sample IDE
  - And topics of Java
    - Data types
    - Expressions
    - Decisions
    - Loops
    - Reading and writing from the console
    - IDE debugging feature
    - Classes, objects and data structures
    - Reading and writing from and to external files
    - Error handling
